      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SMART MISSION (3) scored here this grade first-up and then just missed over 1400m in a CL3. Has the inside gate, and Cormack stays aboard. Fitter again, and he's won over 1600m. He can bounce back for the premier local stable. BOLD BLAZE (6) was outgraded at Eagle Farm, but his form here prior stacks right up. Maps well and switching back to 1600m should go close. SAN JUAN (8) had been threatening here before delivering a Townsville Maiden win over this trip, backed off the map. Has an awkward barrier, but back-to-back wins can't be ruled out.  BO BO BEWARE (4) raced well winning a 62 this track/trip, and then tackled 1800m at Mackay and placed third, well beaten. Maps well, and back home, he can get back on track.",
